Last one need a rebase it conflicts with current master and this patches&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2850&quot; title=&quot;Client support for upstream 3.8 kernel&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2850&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2850&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; kernel: 3.8 upstream kills daemonize()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    kernel_thread() is a low level kernel function.&lt;br/&gt;
    Instead of calling kernel_thread() and relying on daemonize()&lt;br/&gt;
    to create new kernel threads, we should really switch to&lt;br/&gt;
    kthread_run() and elimilate daemonize().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Conflicts:&lt;br/&gt;
        libcfs/autoconf/lustre-libcfs.m4&lt;br/&gt;
        lustre/mdd/mdd_lfsck.c&lt;br/&gt;
        lustre/obdclass/llog_cat.c&lt;br/&gt;
        lustre/ptlrpc/recov_thread.c&lt;/p&gt;


